        "text": "{\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ajayan-a-85836173/\",\"status\":\"follow_only\",\"message\":\"This profile currently exposes Follow but not Connect.\",\"note_sent\":false,\"profile\":\"Ajayan A\\n\\n· 3rd\\n\\nSenior Site Reliability Engineer | Kubernetes, Prometheus, ELK Stack, Loki | 99.99% Uptime Advocate & Toil Reduction Specialist\\n\\nBengaluru, Karnataka, India\\n\\n·\\n\\nContact info\\n\\nIBM\\n\\nKMCT College of Engineering Calicut\\n\\n500+\\n\\nconnections\\n\\nMessage\\nFollow\\nMore\\nAbout\\n\\nSite Reliability Engineer with 11+ years of experience, including 7 years dedicated to SRE practices in dynamic, high-scale environments.\\n\\nIn my recent role, I led the design, implementation, and management of a robust Observability platform using open-source tools (Prometheus, VictoriaMetrics Grafana, and ELK stack). This initiative significantly enhanced system visibility, reduced incident response times, and enabled the organization to define and consistently meet ambitious Service Level Objectives (SLOs)—driving greater reliability and operational excellence.\\n\\nI'm deeply skilled in Linux systems administration, Kubernetes orchestration, and building resilient, scalable Observability Platforms. My approach to SRE blends software engineering with operations: automating toil, optimizing performance, and fostering a culture of blameless post-mortems and continuous improvement.\\n… more\\n\\nTop skills\\n\\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) • prometheus • Kubernetes • Elastic Stack (ELK) • Grafana\\n\\nActivity\\n\\n808 followers\\n\\nFollow\\nPosts\\nComments\\n\\nAjayan A reposted this\\n\\n⎈ Jan-Otto K.\\n\\n \\n • 2nd\\n\\nLiving in Kubernetes since 2016 | CNCF Prometheus Team Member | Grafana Champion | CKS | AWS & Azure Certified\\n\\n5mo • \\n\\n⚠️ CRI-O users, be careful when moving to Kubernetes 1.34\\n\\nIn CRI-O 1.34, image short names are disabled by default. That means something like:\\n\\nimage: nginx\\n\\nwill not pull anymore from Docker Hub (docker.io/library/nginx), because the name is ambiguous in context of CRI-O.\\n\\nInstead, you must write the full image name:\\n\\nimage: docker.io/library/nginx\\n\\n🟩 The reason\\n\\nCRI-O also uses quay.io as a default registry in addition to docker.io. If the image exists in both registries, the pull will fail.\\n\\n🟩 Why this change?\\n\\nCRI-O comes from Red Hat, and they promote their own registry (quay.io) instead of Docker Hub.\\n\\nYou can revert this behavior with a drop-in config at /etc/crio/crio.conf.d/:\\n\\n[crio.image]\\nshort_name_mode = \\\"disabled\\\"\\n\\n🟩 What you should do\\n\\n🔹 Check your manifests and Helm values\\n🔹 Always use full image names including registry\\n🔹 Update your workloads before upgrading your cluster to Kubernetes 1.34\\n\\nAs maintainer of many official Helm Charts, I already see Pull Requests fixing this problem in charts.\\n\\n👉 But please also check your own applications to avoid surprises.\\n… more\\n\\n2,233 reactions\\n2,233\\n\\n73 comments\\n73 comments\\n\\n•\\n\\n330 reposts\\n330 reposts\\n\\nLike\\nComment\\nRepost\\nSend\\n\\nAjayan A\\n\\n • 3rd+\\n\\nSenior Site Reliability Engineer | Kubernetes, Prometheus, ELK Stack, Loki | 99.99% Uptime Advocate & Toil Reduction Specialist\\n\\n7mo • \\n\\nI’m happy to share that I’ve obtained a new certification: 2025 IBMer watsonx Challenge from IBM!\\n\\nCelebrating a new certification\\n\\n30 reactions\\n30\\n\\n4 comments\\n4 comments\\n\\nLike\\nComment\\nRepost\\nSend\\n\\nAjayan A\\n\\n • 3rd+\\n\\nSenior Site Reliability Engineer | Kubernetes, Prometheus, ELK Stack, Loki | 99.99% Uptime Advocate & Toil Reduction Specialist\\n\\n7mo • \\n\\nView my verified achievement from IBM.\\n\\n2025 IBMer watsonx Challenge was issued by IBM to Ajayan A.\\n2025 IBMer watsonx Challenge was issued by IBM to Ajayan A.\\n\\ncredly.com\\n\\n17 reactions\\n17\\n\\nLike\\nComment\\nRepost\\nSend\\n\\nAjayan A reposted this\\n\\nAlex Xu\\n\\n \\n • 3rd+\\n\\n