n Kubernetes • Elastic Stack (ELK) • Kubernetes • Gitlab\\n\\nActivity\\n\\n3,127 followers\\n\\nPosts\\nComments\\nImages\\n\\nMohannad Elewaily reposted this\\n\\nBasil Elghayesh\\n\\n \\n • 2nd\\n\\nProject Manager @ Sonnen  | PMP, PMI-ACP | Agile Project Management\\n\\n3w • Edited • \\n\\nToday, I’m sharing something personal.\\n\\nIn May 2025, I joined Sonnen, one of Shell’s subsidiaries, to help build and lead projects at a time when the company was not yet officially registered with the Egyptian Tax Authority. During that period, our contracts were arranged through a third party while the registration process was being finalized.\\n\\nIn January 2026, after the registration was completed, we were asked to sign new contracts directly with the company.\\n\\nShortly after, I was unexpectedly informed that my role would be terminated. The decision was described as strategic upcoming projects in the pipeline were considered “political,” and leadership was required to be based in Germany.\\n\\nUnder the new contract structure, my employment was treated as if it had just begun, placing me under probation despite having served since May. As a result, the termination came without compensation or transition time.\\n\\nDespite the circumstances, I remain proud of the work I delivered, the structure I built, and the integrity I maintained throughout the journey.\\n\\nI’m now open to new opportunities where I can bring strong project leadership, technical depth, and calm execution under pressure.\\n\\nOnward.\\n… more\\n\\nMohannad Elewaily and 60 others reacted\\nMohannad Elewaily and 60 others\\n\\n13 comments\\n13 comments\\n\\n•\\n\\n13 reposts\\n13 reposts\\n\\nLike\\nComment\\nRepost\\nSend\\n\\nMohannad Elewaily reposted this\\n\\nAbobakr Ahmed\\n\\n • 2nd\\n\\nCloud Native DevOps\\n\\n3w • \\n\\nafter being affected by a recent layoff. DevOps Lead / Senior DevOps Engineer with 6+ years of experience in AWS, Azure, Kubernetes, Terraform, and CI/CD.\\nWorked across